Analyst Consultant - US ABL Lender Consulting Group

Richter Consulting, Inc. (“RCI”) is a member of the Richter Group, one of Canada's largest independent accounting, business advisory and consulting firms. Innovation is the key to our approach, combined with the ability to generate results quickly. Richter offers a full range of advisory and consulting services, supported by in-depth industry knowledge and national and international experience. Our firm, located in Toronto, Montreal, and Chicago, distinguishes itself from all other accounting firms because of the commitment and cooperation of our employees, who are the key to our success. Our clients call upon our experienced professionals to provide our expertise in Business Assessment, Cashflow Forecasting, Financial Reorganization/Profitability Improvement, Crisis Management, Forensic Investigations Support, Transaction Advisory and ABL Diligence, among other services.

A Career With a High Rate Of Return


What’s in it for you?
Opportunity to travel periodically to large cities across the United States;
Gain experience in a specialized consulting practice;
Work within a multidisciplinary team of 20 professionals on stimulating engagements.

Position Overview
Richter Consulting is looking to hire several experienced professionals at the analyst level in their Asset Based Lending diligence practice.

While this position is based in Montreal, our engagements are primarily carried out in major US cities. Our engagements involve a risk-based approach to collateral reviews for leading US financial institutions and are often utilized for refinancing, turnaround situations, liquidations, and/or forensic reviews. Our consultants are required to have a strong audit/accounting background.

Must Haves
CPA required or successful completion of required exams;
Excellent English written and verbal communications skills;
2-5 years of audit or relevant experience;
Ability to rapidly identify key issues during an engagement and make recommendations;
Superior financial analysis skills and proficiency with Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint;
Proficiency with data analysis tools (Power BI, Microsoft Access, and IDEA) an asset;
Strong teamwork and interpersonal skills;
Flexibility to work from home or hybrid work environment
Some US travel required (~20%).
What We Are Looking For


Strong aptitude for quantitative and qualitative analyses and ability to link findings to strategy;
Review and analysis of financial data and trends relating to the collateral and the borrower’s business;
Assessments of collateral borrowing base;
Evaluation of financial reporting systems;
Regular communications with lenders through written reports and exit interviews;
Ability to work autonomously in a fast-paced environment among driven professionals;
Occasional involvement in other engagements such as business assessments, liquidity reviews, monitoring, corporate finance, and due diligence.

What Richter offers you?

Our Montreal office is conveniently located on McGill College. We have regular volunteer opportunities and a variety of team social events. Learning is encouraged, and courses are reimbursed for our team members.

A competitive compensation package, insurance benefits, a retirement savings plan, an employee and family assistance program, a health and well-being program, as well as professional development are also offered. To accommodate your personal and family obligations, a variety of work arrangements are available including a flexible schedule and working remotely.

